One of the commanders of the Biafran Nations League, Henry Edet has been captured by the Rapid dâ€™intervention Battalion (BIR). He was apprehended early Wednesday morning in Atabong East, in the ceded Bakassi Peninsula side of the South West Region of Cameroon. Edet is the operational commander of BnL. The Cameroonian forces picked up Henry Edet in connection with the Black Marine, which is a militant group which has reportedly killed scores of Cameroonian troops. Meanwhile, there has been no official reaction from the leadership of BnL over the development.